        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(workboard): review gate hard blocks + workboard_submit_review tool",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nAgents can call workboard_complete on any card at any time, bypassing the mandatory review gate. This happened in production — cards were marked done without any reviewer session running. The tool layer had no enforcement.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Two cards in the AGENTerprise OS pipeline were marked done without review (protocol violation logs)\n- TypeScript compilation passes locally (0 new errors)\n\n## What This Changes\n\nEnforces Stage 4 REVIEW GATE at the tool level.\n\n### 1. workboard_complete hard blocks\nRejects completion if card status is not review/ready_to_merge/running, or if proof exists but no passed review.\n\n### 2. New tool: workboard_submit_review\nStructured review verdict (approved/changes_requested/blocked), 6 check dimensions, auto-moves card, escalates after 3 failed rounds.\n\n### 3. New status: ready_to_merge\nAdded to WORKBOARD_STATUSES.\n\nFiles: extensions/workboard/src/tools.ts, extensions/workboard/src/types.ts",
